144 #if !defined(REG_READ32)
145  #define REG_READ32(address) (*(volatile uint32_t*)(address))
146 #endif
147 
151 #if !defined(REG_WRITE32)
152  #define REG_WRITE32(address, value) ((*(volatile uint32_t*)(address))= (uint32_t)(value))
153 #endif
154 
158 #if !defined(REG_BIT_SET32)
159  #define REG_BIT_SET32(address, mask) ((*(volatile uint32_t*)(address))|= (uint32_t)(mask))
160 #endif
161 
165 #if !defined(REG_BIT_CLEAR32)
166  #define REG_BIT_CLEAR32(address, mask) ((*(volatile uint32_t*)(address))&= ((uint32_t)~((uint32_t)(mask))))
167 #endif

173 #if !defined(REG_RMW32)
174  #define REG_RMW32(address, mask, value) (REG_WRITE32((address), ((REG_READ32(address)& ((uint32_t)~((uint32_t)(mask))))| ((uint32_t)(value)))))
175 #endif

8570 #define MPU_EAR_EDR_COUNT 5u
8571 #define MPU_RGD_COUNT 16u
8572 #define MPU_RGDAAC_COUNT 16u
8573 
8575 typedef struct {
8576  __IO uint32_t CESR;
8577  uint8_t RESERVED_0[12];
8578  struct { /* offset: 0x10, array step: 0x8 */
8579  __I uint32_t EAR;
8582  __I uint32_t EDR;
8585  } EAR_EDR[MPU_EAR_EDR_COUNT];
8586  uint8_t RESERVED_1[968];
8587  struct { /* offset: 0x400, array step: 0x10 */
8588  __IO uint32_t WORD0;
8589  __IO uint32_t WORD1;
8590  __IO uint32_t WORD2;
8591  __IO uint32_t WORD3;
8592  } RGD[MPU_RGD_COUNT];
8593  uint8_t RESERVED_2[768];
8594  __IO uint32_t RGDAAC[MPU_RGDAAC_COUNT];
8597 } MPU_Type, *MPU_MemMapPtr;
